emu68 Driver Stack @PACKAGE_VERSION@
====================================
AmigaOS drivers for Raspberry Pi 4 / Compute Module 4 running Emu68.


BUILD VARIANT
-------------

  @DEBUG_BACKEND@
  @DEBUG_BACKEND_DESCRIPTION@

The 'off' archive is the normal download. The 'serial' archive is identical
except every driver also emits debug output, for troubleshooting.


COMPONENTS
----------

gic400.library @GIC400_VERSION@ (LIBS:)
  ARM GIC-400 interrupt controller library.
  Required by xhci.device, genet.device, nvme.device, and bcmpcie.library.
  The installer skips this automatically if a copy is already present in ROM
  or an expansion resident module.

bcmpcie.library @BCMPCIE_VERSION@ (LIBS:)
  BCM2711 PCIe bus library. Initialises the PCIe controller, enumerates
  devices, allocates BARs, and provides the driver API.

xhci.device @XHCI_VERSION@ (DEVS:USBHardware/)
  USB 3.0 host controller driver for the VIA VL805 chip present on every
  Raspberry Pi 4 board. Works with the Poseidon USB stack.

genet.device @GENET_VERSION@ (DEVS:Networks/)
  Gigabit Ethernet SANA-II driver for the Genet controller built into
  the Raspberry Pi 4 / CM4.

genet-stats (C:)
  SANA-II statistics viewer for genet.device, installed automatically with
  the driver. Displays live interface counters in a window.

nvme.device @NVME_VERSION@ (DEVS:)
  NVMe storage driver for PCIe-attached NVMe SSDs.

nvmeinfo, nvmeadm (C:)
  Diagnostic and admin CLI tools for nvme.device, installed automatically
  with the driver. nvmeinfo lists NVMe controllers and namespaces; nvmeadm
  reports SMART/health, identify, log pages, self-test, and firmware info.

openpci.library @OPENPCI_VERSION@ (LIBS:) [optional]
  Compatibility shim for software that calls OpenLibrary("openpci.library").
  Forwards calls to bcmpcie.library. Do NOT install if you have a real PCI
  expansion board (Mediator, Prometheus, G-REX, ...).

lspci (C:) [optional]
  CLI tool that lists all devices on the PCIe bus. Run from a Shell to
  verify the PCIe link is up and devices are enumerated correctly.


INSTALLATION
------------

Run the included 'Install' script using the Commodore Installer tool
(v43.3 or later, included with AmigaOS 3.1.4+).

Manual installation: copy files to the destinations listed above and reboot.


REQUIREMENTS
------------

  - Emu68 (https://github.com/michalsc/Emu68) on Raspberry Pi 4 or CM4
  - AmigaOS 3.x
  - USB stack (for xhci.device)
  - A TCP/IP stack such as Roadshow (for genet.device)


